	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Yo quiero Pachelbel: Spot that chord progression</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The piece I chose to <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=173778#p173778" class="postlink">demonstrate vibrato in the Pently music engine</a> was <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pachelbel%27s_Canon" class="postlink">Johann Pachelbel's &quot;Canon in D&quot;</a>. This piece is notorious for popularizing the I-V-vi-iii-IV-V-IV-V chord progression, as explained in Rob Paravonian's <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JdxkVQy7QLM" class="postlink">Pachelbel Rant</a>.<br /><br />The whole Canon is <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=134597#p134597" class="postlink">included in <em>Might and Magic</em></a>, and the progression can be heard in <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LOd7gzpFl-A#t=12" class="postlink">one of the music selections from <em>Pipe Dream</em></a>. Where else in NES music have you encountered the progression?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


